article.headline: Weber State 58, Portland 51
article.story: OGDEN, Utah (AP) -- Nic Sparrow scored 13 points and Pat Danley had nine points and 10 rebounds in Weber State's 58-51 win over Portland on Tuesday. Slobodan Ocokoljic and John Hamilton scored 12 points apiece for the Wildcats (5-3), who held on for the win with some clutch free throw shooting. Portland (5-3) had some opportunities in the final minute, but shot a couple of airballs on consecutive possessions. Eugene Jeter had 20 points and Donald Wilson added 17 for Portland. Casey Frandsen, who scored 21 for Portland against Weber State last year, was held to one point Tuesday. Weber State has won all six meetings between the schools. The Wildcats hit only 16-of-29 free throws, but forced 22 turnovers.
